# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (refactoring code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating dependencies, build tasks etc; no production code change)
#    content  (adding or updating blog content or projects)
#    design   (UI/UX improvements)
# --------------------
# Scope is the specific component or section impacted, e.g.:
#    blog     (blog post or blog functionality)
#    project  (project pages or functionality)
#    layout   (site layout components)
#    comp     (UI components)
#    api      (external API integration)
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#    Use imperative mood in the subject line ("Add" not "Added")
#    Do not end the subject line with a period
#    Separate subject from body with a blank line
